Source: AMC (amc.org.au/assessment/fees 2024-25 schedule): CAT MCQ=AUD$2720 Clinical=AUD$4090; AHPRA (ahpra.gov.au/Registration/Fees 2024-25): limited registration=AUD$855/yr initial & renewal; Dept of Home Affairs (immi.homeaffairs.gov.au 2024-25): Subclass 482 (medium-term stream)=AUD$2645 Subclass 189=AUD$4640; OET (occupationalenglishtest.org): AUD$587; IELTS India (ielts.org): ~INR17000; OSHC (Allianz/Medibank/Bupa OSHC comparison Feb 2026): single basic ~AUD$4800 standard ~AUD$5500 premium ~AUD$6500/yr; AMC Skills Assessment for migration: ~AUD$500; AMC coaching (Academically.com.au ACE-theExam.com.au SwagAcademy PrepMatch various Indian providers): INR50k-150k; Indian PCC (passportindia.gov.in): INR500 official + processing ~INR3k-5k total; Panel physician medical exam (Delhi/Mumbai/Chennai/Kolkata): INR10k-15k; Flights (Skyscanner/Google Flights Feb 2026 Delhi/Mumbai to Sydney/Melbourne economy return): INR50k-90k
Notes: COMPONENT COLUMN VALUES = typical/single-attempt scenario at AUD/INR 64.00 (Feb 2026 mid-market rate from Wise/XE). MIN/TYPICAL/MAX totals reflect different scenarios as follows. --- MIN SCENARIO (INR 1176760): 1× AMC CAT MCQ (174080) + 1× AMC Clinical (261760) + IELTS not OET (17000) + AHPRA initial reg (54720) + AHPRA renewal yr1 (54720) + Skills assessment (32000) + Subclass 482 visa (169280) + NO PR visa (0) + Basic OSHC single AUD4800 (307200) + Budget travel 1 trip (50000) + Budget accommodation (35000) + No coaching (0) + PCC (3000) + Medical exam (10000) + Misc (8000) = INR 1176760. --- TYPICAL SCENARIO (INR 1584008): 1× CAT MCQ (174080) + 1.5× avg Clinical attempts (392640) + OET (37568) + AHPRA initial (54720) + AHPRA renewal yr1 (54720) + Skills assessment (32000) + Visa 482 (169280) + NO PR (0) + Standard OSHC AUD5500 (352000) + Travel 1 trip (70000) + Standard accommodation (50000) + Mid coaching (65000) + PCC (5000) + Medical (12000) + Misc (15000) = INR 1584008. --- MAX SCENARIO (INR 2442928): 2× CAT MCQ (348160) + 2× Clinical (523520) + OET (37568) + AHPRA initial (54720) + AHPRA renewal yr1 (54720) + Skills assessment (32000) + Visa 482 (169280) + Visa 189/190 PR (296960) + Premium OSHC AUD6500 (416000) + Travel 2 trips (180000) + Premium accommodation 2 trips (140000) + Full coaching (150000) + PCC (5000) + Medical (15000) + Misc (20000) = INR 2442928. --- KEY NOTES: (1) Certificate of Sponsorship/nomination for 482 visa is typically paid by employer — NOT included in migrant costs. (2) State/territory nomination fee for 190 visa (~AUD300-330) NOT separately included — absorbed in misc for Max scenario. (3) AHPRA Annual Renewal is a recurring cost — Year 1 included in all scenarios; ongoing renewals modelled separately. (4) OSHC or equivalent private health insurance is MANDATORY for 482 visa holders — not optional unlike UK NHS entitlement. (5) AMC Clinical Exam held at AMC National Examination Centre in Melbourne — travel to Melbourne mandatory. (6) Skills assessment by AMC required for 482 visa in ANZSCO 2531xx medical practitioner occupations. (7) AMC exam fees confirmed from amc.org.au fee schedule — may increase annually verify before applying. (8) AMC Clinical pass rate historically ~50% — most candidates benefit from structured coaching. (9) Subclass 482 medium-term stream applies to medical practitioners (ANZSCO 253111-253999); allows pathway to PR via Subclass 186 (employer-sponsored) after 2 years. (10) Subclass 189/190 included in Max scenario as alternative PR pathway via SkillSelect points system.
